programme.title: (Subbed) Igor ThiagoThe Big Interview
programme.desc: Few players have had a journey to the Premier League like Brentford's Igor Thiago. Ten years ago, he was working as a bricklayer on the outskirts of Brasilia to support his family. Fast forward a decade, with stops at Ludogorets and Club Brugge in between, he is second only to Erling Haaland in Premier League goals this season, after a debut campaign disrupted by injury. This week, the Big Interview sits down with the Bees' number nine to discuss his unusual route to the Premier League, overcoming adversity and his hopes for the future.?

programme.title: (Subbed) Eden HazardPremier League Hall Of FamePl Stories
programme.desc: We sit down for an exclusive interview with the first of two new Premier League Hall of fame inductees, Eden Hazard. A celebrated footballer who lit up the English top-flight during his illustrious career; a winner of multiple domestic and European honours, he became a true legend of the Premier League era. He reflects on his rise to the top, the moments that defined his career, and the immense pride he feels at joining the elite ranks of the Premier League's greatest ever players.

programme.title: Yakubu1-To-11
programme.desc: Known simply as 'The Yak,' Yakubu takes on 1-to-11, selecting his ultimate lineup from the best players he shared the pitch with. A powerhouse striker with 95 Premier League goals across spells at Portsmouth, Middlesbrough, Everton, and Blackburn, he reflects on the teammates who made the biggest impression during his career. Expect a team full of strength, flair, and goalscoring pedigree.

Maggie, who passed away in September 2024, is beloved the world over for her countless iconic screen performances - in recent years she gained a new level of popularity playing the razor-tongued Lady Violet Crawley in Downton Abbey, but Maggie remained a very private person who had little time for the trappings that came with fame in spite of her success. Using Maggie's own voice as its heartbeat - and featuring personal accounts from close friends and colleagues from across her career - the film tells the story of a girl born in pre-war Essex who took Broadway and the West End by storm against the odds before eventually becoming one of the nation's most popular and respected performers.
